Dear Andy 
 
Thank you for a lovely day yesterday. 
I do enjoy your and Simon's company and Mr Hignett turned out to be a good bloke too. 
In respect of Infra Projects I have to confess to my second mistake of the year. 
At least like the previous one it is in your favour. 
The calculation on the first loan is correct. 
The RCF calculation is wrong so I will explain what I did. 
When Gary first took out the facility we advanced 25k from OSBF funds and then ADW Enterprises did the second 15k. 
The interest payment from Infra for the RCF was 900 (2.25% of 40000). 
OSBF paid over 540 to ADW (900 x 1.35/2.25) not taking into account that 25k of the loan is OSBF capital. 
The payment should have been 202.50 and not 540 an error of 337.50 for which I apologise. 
Thank you for letting me know. 
Would you like to send us back the 337.50 or shall we adjust it on next months? 
It might work better if you could transfer it back as I think Gary intends to repay the balances before the end of September so we may have had the last interest payment. 
As promised I will work more on Silk Investments (Glossop) Limited today. 
I had a good chat with Sam Hinchliffe yesterday evening and he is sending over further details on his and Ged's construction experience.
